'''Dirk Demol''' (born 4 November 1959 in [[Kuurne]], [[Belgium]]) is [[directeur sportif]] for [[UCI World Tour]] team [[Trek–Segafredo (men's team)|Trek–Segafredo]]. His specialization as a director is the spring classics, having himself won the 1988 edition of the one-day classic [[Paris–Roubaix]], riding as a professional cyclist for Team ADR.
