{{Infobox officeholder |name = Maher El-Beheiry |birthname = |image = |office1 = President of the [[Supreme Constitutional Court of Egypt]] |term_start1 = 1 July 2012 |term_end1 = 1 July 2013 |predecessor2 = [[Farouk Sultan]] |successor2 = [[Adly Mansour]]<ref name=HCC>{{cite web|title=Current Members of the Court |url=http://hccourt.gov.eg/CourtMembers/CurrentCourt.asp |publisher=[[Supreme Constitutional Court of Egypt]] |accessdate=3 July 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130510210107/http://www.hccourt.gov.eg/CourtMembers/CurrentCourt.asp |archivedate=10 May 2013 |df= }}</ref> |appointed2 = [[Mohamed Morsi]] |religion = [[Sunni Islam|Islam]] }}
'''Maher El-Beheiry''' ({{lang-ar|ماهر البحيري}}) was President of the [[Supreme Constitutional Court of Egypt]]. He succeeded [[Farouk Sultan]] as president of the court on 1 July 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=El-Beheiry to replace Farouk Sultan at helm of Egypt constitutional court|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/News/43314.aspx|work=Ahram Online|publisher=[[Al-Ahram]]|accessdate=3 July 2013|date=30 May 2012}}</ref> He served for a year, until 1 July 2013, when he was succeeded by [[Adly Mansour]].<ref name=HCC/><ref>{{cite web|title=Morsi appoints new head of constitutional court |url=http://www.expatcairo.com/2013/05/morsi-appoints-new-head-of-constitutional-court/ |publisher=Expat Cairo |accessdate=3 July 2013 |date=20 May 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130703202156/http://www.expatcairo.com/2013/05/morsi-appoints-new-head-of-constitutional-court/ |archivedate=3 July 2013 |df= }}</ref> For a time during the [[2013 Egyptian coup d'état]], some organizations reported El-Beheiry as having been selected for the position of acting [[President of Egypt]].<ref>http://www.businessinsider.com/maher-el-beheiry-egypts-new-leader-2013-7</ref> However, these reports were incorrect: Mansour, the current court president, was selected as acting president.
