'''Pauline Musters''' (February 26, 1876&nbsp;– March 1, 1895) at {{convert|24|in|cm}} tall, is recognized by the [[Guinness Book of Records]] as the shortest woman ever recorded<ref name="GWR">{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/shortest-woman-ever|title=Shortest woman ever|work=Guinness World Records|accessdate=August 31, 2018}}</ref>.

Born in [[Ossendrecht]], The [[Netherlands]] on February 26, 1876, she died in [[New York City]] at the age of 19 from a combination of [[pneumonia]] and [[meningitis]]. At the time of her death, she measured exactly 61&nbsp;cm (24&nbsp;in) tall.<ref name="GWR"/>

